Senior citizens in Edo State who thronged the Edo Specialist Hospital (ESH) to take advantage of the hospital’s free medical services, including consultancy and screening, have hailed the management of the hospital on the exercise. <img class="alignnone wp-image-1265790 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=640%2C428&#038;ssl=1" alt="Edo Specialist Hospital’s free healthcare exercise excites the elderly in Edo" width="640" height="428" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=300%2C201&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=768%2C514&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=1024%2C685&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=260%2C174&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=194%2C130&amp;ssl=1 194w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?resize=560%2C375&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/IMG_4-1.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  The hospital management opened its doors as early as 7 a.m. on October 1, to a crowd of senior citizens in Edo State, to mark the International Day for Older Persons. A cross-section of the beneficiaries expressed satisfaction with the love, care, and attention shown to them by the ESH staff, describing it like a first-time experience in healthcare service in the state. A retiree, who identified himself as Mr. Omoruyi, looked forward to revisiting the hospital for medical care in the future. Mr. Osifo, another patient, said, “I am really happy with my checkup, I will ensure I come back and also refer others to this hospital”. The hospital’s world-class geriatricians, as well as other medical practitioners, provided the free-of-charge services, including blood pressure and sugar tests, respiratory rate and heart rate checks, among others to the beneficiaries. Medical consultations and services such as x-rays and malaria tests were also offered to patients who were diagnosed with various health conditions. The patients were informed about the hospital’s specialised services such as ENT (Ear, Nose, and Throat), Nephrology, Dialysis, Geriatrics and other services including laboratory tests and mammography. According to the management, “As ESH plans to operate 24-hours, additional services will include ophthalmology and minor surgeries. vanguard FORMER President of the National Union of Petroleum and Natural Gas Workers, NUPENG and a member of the House of Representative, representing Akoko-Edo, Federal Constituency of Edo state, Comrade Peter Akpatason, has embarked on free medical service for the people of the constituency to boost their access to quality healthcare… December 13, 2011 In "Health" FEDERAL Government-owned Irrua Specialist Teaching Hospital, Irrua, Edo State, has recorded a medical feat after it successfully carried out medical surgery on hips and knees replacement on some of its patients. November 4, 2015 In "News" Edo State Governor, Mr. Godwin Obaseki, has promised to sustain investment in critical sectors of the state; education, infrastructure, security and job creation initiatives to retain his administration’s positive growth trajectory. January 1, 2019 In "News"